# 5.15 Design Philosophy

Each component was intentionally designed to be:

- Independent
- Replaceable
- Testable
- Deployable

Examples:

- Flask can be replaced with FastAPI.
- Gemini can be replaced with another supported model.
- Tavily can be replaced with a different search provider.
- Filesystem MCP can be replaced with cloud storage.
- Scholarship MCP can be extended or replaced without affecting the rest of the application.

This modularity is one of the project's strongest architectural characteristics.

---

# 5.16 Key Takeaways

Every major component has a single responsibility.

The presentation layer, orchestration layer, reasoning layer, execution layer, and deployment layer remain independent.

This separation made it possible to:

- Debug each MCP server individually.
- Validate deployments incrementally.
- Replace infrastructure components without redesigning the application.

The resulting architecture is modular, extensible, and representative of modern enterprise AI systems built around reasoning models augmented with specialized execution tools.